text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events:

The "Beer for Taxation" parade moving westward on Central Park South (W. 59th Street) in one of the greatest demonstrations in the City's history, demanding that beer be legalized as an aid to relieve the Depression. Over 100,000 New Yorkers participated in the Parade led by Mayor James J. Walker.

May 14, 1932
title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal Events - Beer Parade.

text:
Central Park, as seen from Rockefeller Center, (Radio City). Also shown is a general view of midtown Manhattan between the Hudson (left) and East (right) Rivers. Silhouetted against the Park is the West 59th skyline, consisting of the Essex House, Barbizon Plaza, N. Y. Athletic Club and the Plaza Hotel buildings.

About 1934.

Rockefeller Center
Hamilton Wright
title: Manhattan: Central Park - [General view] from Rockefeller Center, Radio City.

text:
A general view northward from atop the 70 storied R.C.A. Building at Rockefeller Plaza, showing Central Park lying in the center of Manhattan. Fifth Ave is to the right and Central Park West to the left. The southern boundary is Central Park South (West 59th St.). Upon the latter appear the tall structures. The North (Hudson) River, the George Washington Bridge, and the New Jersey coast line are in the left background.

W. P. A. Photo
Federal Writers Project

1936
title: General view - [Midtown Manhattan - Rockefeller Plaza from R.C.A. Building.]
